<paragraph blockId="18.[189,1399,920,1304]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
This species was described based on male and female specimens collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1132,1250,920,946]" name="Honduras" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Honduras</collectingCountry>
. The female 
<typeStatus box="[189,292,959,985]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected on March 30 at Escuela Agrícola Panamericana by Rua Williams, the wife of the American explorer and botanist Louis Otho Williams, who worked on the flora of Central America (
<bibRefCitation author="Burger" box="[197,351,1039,1065]" firstAuthor="Burger" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="355 - 356" refId="ref19240" refString="Burger W. 1991. Louis Otho Williams (1908 - 1991). Taxon 40: 355 - 356." type="journal article" year="1991">Burger 1991</bibRefCitation>
). According to the original description, the type series was composed of another female specimen collected by Adan Rivera on April 8 and two males collected by Wilmatte P. Cockerell and Adan Rivera on January 28. The 
<typeStatus box="[574,677,1118,1144]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[692,777,1118,1144]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 13. Centris ruae Cockerell, 1949, holotype, ♀ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534212). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722976/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) is currently housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1050,1140,1119,1145]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and has the following data label: Zamorano 
<collectingCountry box="[452,566,1158,1184]" name="Honduras" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Honduras</collectingCountry>
March 30 Mrs. Williams [handwritten]\ 
